This project focuses on identifying, analyzing, and monitoring fraudulent transactions using data analytics and business intelligence tools. The objective is to detect suspicious patterns, reduce financial losses, and improve decision-making through data-driven insights.

🎯 Objectives

Detect fraudulent transactions in real-time or batch analysis

Identify high-risk customers, regions, and transaction types

Monitor fraud trends over time

Improve fraud prevention strategies

📌 Key KPIs (Key Performance Indicators)
1. Fraud Rate (%)

Definition: Percentage of fraudulent transactions over total transactions

Formula:

Fraud Rate = (Fraud Transactions / Total Transactions) * 100
2. Total Fraud Transactions

Total number of transactions flagged as fraud

3. Total Transaction Volume

Total number of transactions processed

4. Fraud Loss Amount

Total monetary loss due to fraudulent transactions

5. Average Fraud Transaction Value

Formula:

Avg Fraud Value = Fraud Loss Amount / Fraud Transactions
6. Detection Rate

Percentage of frauds successfully identified

7. False Positive Rate

Legitimate transactions incorrectly flagged as fraud

8. Fraud by Category (% Contribution)

Contribution of each category/type to total fraud

9. High-Risk Customer Count

Number of customers with repeated or suspicious activities

10. Fraud Trend (MoM / YoY)

Month-over-Month or Year-over-Year fraud growth

